author: How a fight turned into a horror for a promising young boxer
title: Tennis - Japan's Doi wins first career title in Luxembourg
text:
Tennis - Japan's Doi wins first career title in Luxembourg AFP 1 hr ago Â© Provided by AFP Japan's Kurumi Nara hits a return against compatriot Misaki Doi during their women's singles first round match at the Pan Pacific Open tennis tournament in Tokyo on September 22, 2015. AFP PHOTO / KAZUHIRO NOGI Japan's world number 92 Misaki Doi claimed her first career title with a 6-4, 6-7 (7/9), 6-0 win over Germany's Mona Barthel in the final of the Luxembourg Open. Left-hander Doi, 24, finished the fresher of the two women having played just one set in her semi-final on Saturday when Belgian opponent Alison Van Uytvanck retired with an injury. World number 55 Barthel had been aiming for a fourth title after claiming Bastad in 2014, Paris in 2013 and Hobart in 2012.
